Coloration. Formalin-fixed, alcohol-preserved specimens grey dorsally, progressively lighter towards abdomen; fin edges tinged black. Outer edge of each scale with speckled densely with melanophores, giving it a dark appearance (
Fig. 3
). In life, head and body overall silvery-grey, each scale with a dark outer edge; a black bar behind the opercle, prominent in juveniles (less than ~ 100 mm SL), becoming progressively fainter in mature specimens. All fins pale yellow; red pigments present on interradial membranes of large adults (larger than ~ 200 mm SL).
